According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Antionum''' ({{IPAc-en|Àå|√¶|n|t|i|Àà|o ä|n|…ô|m}})<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from ¬´ƒÉn-tƒì-≈ç¬¥num¬ª</ref> was a [[Nephite]] military commander under the [[prophet]]-general [[Mormon (Book of Mormon prophet)|Mormon]] and lived during the 4th century.  During the final war between the [[Nephites]] and the [[Lamanites]], at the cataclysmic [[Battle of Cumorah]], Antionum and his entire army of ten thousand men were killed, along with the other dozens of Nephite military commanders and their armies of ten thousand apiece.  The Battle of Cumorah marked the end of the Nephite civilization.

