'''Atanatiya Sutta''' is the 32nd Sutta described in the [[Digha Nikaya]] ("Long Discourses of [[Gautama Buddha|Buddha]]").<ref>{{cite book|last=Walshe|first=Maurice|title=The Long Discourses of the Buddha: A Translation of the Digha Nikaya|year=1995|publisher=Wisdom Publications|pages=471‚Äì478}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/dn/dn.32.0.piya.html|title=Atanatiya Sutta: Discourse on Atanatiya |publisher = Buddhist Publication Society|date=1999}}</ref> It is a poem for protection from evil spirits presented to Buddha by King [[Vai≈õrava·πáa|Vessavana]].

