{{Expand Japanese|ËÅûÂæóÂ§ßÂêõ|date=July 2017}} {{nihongo|'''Kikoe-≈çgimi'''|ËÅûÂæóÂ§ßÂêõ|}} was the highest ranking ''[[Noro (priestess)|noro priestess]]'' of the [[Ryukyuan religion]] during the period of the [[Ryukyu Kingdom]].
The position of kikoe-≈çgimi was formally established during the reign of King [[Sh≈ç Shin]] (r. 1477-1526) in order to centralize the religious order. Only a royal woman could be appointed to the position of kikoe-≈çgimi.
After Ryukyu's annexation by Japan in 1879, this position was formally abolished, but the last kikoe-≈çgimi continued her role until her death in 1944.
